OL,3,CUK inflation remains steady for May,
OL,4,Cagainst expectations
OL,6,FOfgem lowered its energy price cap
OL,7,Ffrom the start of April by 7%, or #10
OL,8,Fa month, for the average household
OL,9,Fusing both electricity and gas,
OL,10,Ffollowing government measures to
OL,11,Freduce bills.
OL,13,FIt meant that inflation declined for
OL,14,Fthat month, despite a jump in fuel
OL,15,Fcosts caused by the conflict in the
OL,16,FMiddle East.
OL,18,FCommenting on Wednesday's inflation
OL,19,Ffigures, ONS Chief Economist Grant
OL,20,FFitzner said:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1781694173
OL,3,CUK inflation remains steady for May,
OL,4,Cagainst expectations
OL,6,F"After last month's slowdown,
OL,7,Finflation held steady in May as
OL,8,Fvarious price movements offset each
OL,9,Fother.
OL,11,F"The main upward movement came from
OL,12,Ftransport with airfares, vehicle taxes
OL,13,Fand petrol prices all pushing up
OL,14,Finflation.
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1781694173
OL,3,CUK inflation remains steady for May,
OL,4,Cagainst expectations
OL,6,F"These were offset by lower food
OL,7,Fprices, with decreases in inflation
OL,8,Fseen across a range of meat, dairy and
OL,9,Fvegetable items compared to last
OL,10,Fmonth, as well as the cost of domestic
OL,11,Fheating oil, which fell back after
OL,12,Fclimbing in recent month.
OL,14,F"The annual cost of raw materials
OL,15,Fcontinued to increase, led by rises in
OL,16,Fthe cost of chemicals, while the
OL,17,Fincrease in the costs of goods leaving
OL,18,Ffactories slowed, partly due to a drop
OL,19,Fin the cost of domestically produced
OL,20,Fcars."
